&lt;p&gt;We are Suffolk Primary care. A partnership of 13 like-minded practices at the forefront of change we share resources knowledge and skills to collaborate and build capability as well as capacity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, team focused individual to join our team of bank Care Navigators. You would have the opportunity to work at any of our sites across Suffolk on a regular or ad-hoc basis working alongside friendly and committed colleagues. We are able to offer flexible working/hoursand the opportunity to work on the frontline of primary care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be able to demonstrate excellent communication skills, have the ability to remain calm under pressure and be able to multi-task .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous experience of working within a GP Practice environment and a working knowledge of SystmOne would be a definite advantage.&lt;/p&gt;
